Regional Insights
•	North America: Dominates the market due to robust research infrastructure, high adoption of advanced technologies, and significant investments in biotechnology.
•	Europe: Follows closely with growing investments in personalized medicine and biopharmaceuticals.
•	Asia-Pacific: Emerging as a lucrative market due to increasing R&D activities, government initiatives to boost biotechnology, and the expansion of biomanufacturing facilities.
Future Trends
1.	Integration with AI and IoT: The incorporation of artificial intelligence (AI) and the Internet of Things (IoT) into biosensors is expected to enable predictive analytics and remote monitoring.
2.	Miniaturization and Portability: Advances in material sciences are leading to smaller, more portable biosensors suitable for diverse applications.
3.	Customizable Solutions: Manufacturers are increasingly offering tailored solutions for specific research and production needs.
